<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="597" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,258,1471]" pageId="7" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1410,1435]" pageId="7" pageNumber="597">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[848,915,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="597">longi-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[969,1084,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="597">maculatus</emphasis>
, referring to the black elongate triangular blotch in the forewing.
</paragraph>
